{
  "text": "The bounds come from two classes of experiments: atmospheric neutrino oscillation measurements, mainly driven by the IceCube [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] observations, and probes using accelerator neutrinos, such as in the MINOS+ case [CITATION_3] . Atmospheric data, thanks to the strong matter effects that influence neutrino oscillations through Earth, can constrain |U \u00b54 | 2 and to a minor extent also |U \u03c4 4 | 2 , in particular thanks to the low-energy data by the Deep-Core section of the IceCube detector [CITATION_4] . Bounds on |U \u00b54 | 2 are however approximately one order of magnitude stronger than those on |U \u03c4 4 | 2 .",
